<br>
pt 1 dueling a bard (my sister)<br>
<br>
1) if we are in a restricted area, i.e. ec tunnel, i can take her down w/o going beyond half life 80% of the time or so<br>
<br>
2) anything more open than say 80ft any direction she will be able to kite/joust me w/o losing more than 2 bubs of life w/o using her heal song.<br>
<br>
3)if sbd procs or they get snared any bard is screwed as it becomes soooo much easier for me to get a backstab off, engulfing darkness stick or snare/root pois = dead bard<br>
<br>
4)hide does not work if her aoe is memmed<br>
<br>
5)hide does you no good if they sing dd song, it will land whether you hide or not alot of the time for some odd reason<br>
<br>
6)running won't do you any good unless you confuse them as to which way you are going (this is where hide comes in handy) because they will snare you, in order to get away get unsnared silly =P<br>
<br>
Pt2 rog v bard PvP<br>
<br>
ok little harder on sullon because they will be any range to you, greens are easy to take down one bs does wonders reds its best  to run and pray because their songs will kill you in like 40sec if they are twice your lvl like they normally are to me =P, but now i will go into pvp an even bard<br>
<br>
1) surprise is a rogs friend, if they catch you unawares run away and come back later, or be brave and prepare to die<br>
<br>
2)lots of the same applies in pvp as in duel, restricted areas are your friends, anything wider than 80ft or so will get you killed fast unless they are at less than half life, even then they hurt alot or will just run away. Best to have some sort of snare/root handy and doesn't hurt to have sow or jboots =)<br>
<br>
3)jousting is an effective tactic but be aware of what they are wielding, and keep in mind backstab is the only way your going to take them down besides snare/root<br>
<br>
4) if they are under 1/4 stick to them like glue, the more hp you take the less chance of them getting away, they know this and will try running once down this far, big mistake if in enclosed area its backstab time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
